The paper deals with compressed sensing and sparse signal estimation, which are core topics in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new measure of sparsity and proposes a new algorithm for solving sparse signal estimation problems, which are relevant to the Learning (cs.LG), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Systems and Control (cs.SI) sub-categories.
